title: Cheryl and Liam Payne's baby due within weeks as pair prepare for new arrival
text:
Cheryl and Liam Payne's baby due within weeks as pair prepare for new arrival There were rumours that the star had already gone into labour Share Liam and Cheryl's baby is due within weeks Share Get daily     
Cheryl 's baby is due within weeks. 
The singer and her One Direction star boyfriend Liam Payne are set to welcome their first child into the world in March. 
Rumours have been rife that Cheryl was in labour - with some even believing that she'd actually given birth - but the star reportedly still has a few weeks to go. 
"The rumour mill has been rife that the birth is imminent and there have even been claims she’s in labour already but that’s not the case at all," a source told The Sun . Read More Cheryl and Liam Payne 'move in their mums to help with their new baby' Liam Payne and Cheryl are set to become parents very soon (Photo: Getty Images Europe) 
"She’s still a little way off and has been enjoying the build-up as well as focusing on her charity announcement which is a really big deal for her. 
"It was important for her to continue working throughout her pregnancy, Cheryl’s Trust was her top priority." 
Earlier today, the star broke her Twitter silence to share some happy news with her fans. 
The star hasn't tweeted since December, last year, but took to the social media site this morning to make an announcement. 
The Geordie star told her followers that after working hard for five years, she's finally found a site in Newcastle where a Prince's Trust centre can be opened.
